        "discriminators": [
          "The SIZZLE of frying is the dominant real morphology: a dense, near-stationary high-frequency crackle texture — a very high onset_rate_per_second of micro-events, high high_band_energy, essentially no pitch, low crest. It is the same physical event as FIRE-SIZZLE (steam bursting out of oil) and signal analysis cannot separate the two; only the kitchen context in the name can.",
          "Chopping is the other half of the subcategory: hard, roughly periodic impulses with a board resonance under them — a completely different morphology, which caps this at narrowable. Boiling is bubbling and will score toward WATER-BUBBLES.",
          "A recording of the pan or pot itself being moved or set down is FOOD & DRINK-KITCHENWARE, not COOKING."
        ],
